<p><strong>Services Marketing, 6th Edition by Zeithaml: Questions and Answers</strong></p>
<p><strong>1. What are the five dimensions of service quality in Zeithaml's model?</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Tangibles</li>
<li>Reliability</li>
<li>Responsiveness</li>
<li>Assurance</li>
<li>Empathy</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>2. Explain the concept of a service blueprint.</strong>
A service blueprint is a visual representation of a service process that maps out the sequence of interactions between customers and service providers, as well as the supporting processes behind the scenes.</p>
<p><strong>3. What is the role of segmentation in services marketing?</strong>
Segmentation involves dividing a customer base into distinct groups based on shared characteristics or needs. It allows businesses to tailor their marketing efforts to specific market segments.</p>
<p><strong>4. Describe the "moments of truth" in customer interactions.</strong>
Moments of truth are critical touchpoints in the customer journey where customers form impressions of the service experience. These moments determine whether the customer will develop a positive or negative perception of the brand.</p>
<p><strong>5. How does technology impact services marketing?</strong>
Technology has revolutionized the way services are delivered, marketed, and consumed. It enables businesses to enhance customer experiences, improve efficiency, and reach a wider audience through digital channels.</p>